{
  "text": "OTU clustering was performed using USEARCH [CITATION_1] , which included: 1. Dereplication and subsequent error-correction by outputting the consensus sequences of an initial clustering-step at 97% identity. 2. Removing chimeric sequences using UCHIME [CITATION_2] by comparison to the chimera-free Greengenes database (version 13_05; http://greengenes.lbl.gov/) [CITATION_3] clustered at 97% identity. 3. A final OTU clustering step at 97% identity. The parameters for chimera detection were set to ignore low-divergence chimeras by disregarding OTUs with at least 97% identity to a sequence in the database and increase sensitivity to higher-divergence chimeras (UCHIME parameters:-minh 0.22-mindiv 3-mindiffs 5).",
